<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Borussia Dortmund suffered their first defeat of the new Bundesliga season following a 2-0 defeat at Augsburg.</p>

<p>Felix Uduokhai and Daniel Caligiuri scored one goal each as the hosts went top of the Bundesliga table in a frustrating afternoon for the likes of Jadon Sancho and Erling Haaland.</p>

<p>Dortmund were also left aggrieved when they were denied a second-half penalty for a foul on Giovanni Reyna, but Lucien Favre's men nonetheless dropped points for the first time this season after beating Borussia Moenchengladbach last weekend.</p>

<p>More to follow </p>

<p>Jude Bellingham and Borussia Dortmund suffered a shock first defeat of the Bundesliga season</p>

<p>Felix Uduokhai scored just before half-time in Augsburg's win against Lucien Favre's men</p>

<p>Daniel Caligiuri then scored the second on the break early on in the second half for Augsburg</p>

<p>Jadon Sancho and Dortmund had good first-half opportunities but were ultimately frustrated</p>

<p>Fans were once again back in stadiums in Bavaria and were observing social distancing </p>

<p>Tempers also flared during both halves between Erling Haaland and Augsburg's opponents</p>

<p>But having won the game for Dortmund there last season, Haaland could not score this time</p>

<p>Augsburg defended brilliantly and ensured Emre Can and his team-mates could not score</p>

<p>Frustration increased when they were denied a penalty for an alleged foul on Giovanni Reyna</p>

<p>But it was just not meant to be for Mats Hummels and co. as they dropped three points</p>
